Unique key stores only distinct values, no duplicate/identical values will be stored.
a table can have or can't have a unique key.It is not compulsory.
a table can have multiple columns with unique key.
It can accept null value. But only one null value per column.
we can create table even without using any unique key. It is not compulsory.
we can add unique key for those columns also which are not defined with auto_increment constants. 
unique key can be made as foreign key in another table.
unique key can used on those columns also which are defined or not defined wuith auto_increment constraint. Not a issue.
We can able to drop/delete primary key after table creation.
We can add primary key in a table by 2 ways- while creating table and also by alter the existing table later.
